<h1>Usage options</h1>

<h2>Chrome Extension</h2>
<p>This gives you the full experience that we envisioned for the elderly users who might have trouble with bookmarklets</p>
<ol>
  <li>Download the zipped extension: <a href="/download/techConnect_chr.zip">Not up yet</a></li>
  <li>Unpack the extension</li>
  <li>Go to <a href="chrome://extensions/">chrome://extensions/</a> and click "Load unpacked extension". Select the folder you unpacked the extension into</li>
  <li>TechConnect extension is now installed (can click on its icon)</li>
</ol>

<h2>Here is a bookmarklet</h2>
<p>You can drag it to your bookmarks bar, or right-click and bookmark the link.</p>
<div>
  <a href="javascript:(function() {
    var script=document.createElement('script');
    script.type='text/javascript';
    script.src='<%= request.base_url %>/quokka';
    document.body.appendChild(script);
  })();">TechConnect Bookmarklet (Drag me to your bookmarks bar)</a>
</div>
<p>Now, you can click on the bookmark to launch it on any page</p>

<h2>For the truly lazy</h2>
You can just click on <a href="javascript:(function() {
    var script=document.createElement('script');
    script.type='text/javascript';
    script.src='<%= request.base_url %>/quokka';
    document.body.appendChild(script);
  })();">this TechConnect link</a> without saving it anywhere. You don't get to see it run on top of another page this way though.

